<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
strcmp(stream->stream_name, Filename) can read past the end of either operand if that operand is not terminated within its object bounds. stream->stream_name is a fixed-size array (char[OS_MAX_PATH_LEN]) but the code does not prove it is NUL-terminated; Filename is only checked for non-NULL and may point to a non-terminated or out-of-bounds buffer. If stream_name was populated with a fixed-length copy without ensuring a terminating '\0' (or Filename is not NUL-terminated), strcmp will scan past the array and access memory beyond the object bounds. The call should instead bound the comparison (e.g. strncmp with OS_MAX_PATH_LEN and ensure NUL-termination) or otherwise guarantee both strings are NUL-terminated within their buffers.
</scenario>
